	quest.2E17BF74F0DD6A58.quest_desc: ["a stable propeller bearing for helicopters. the bearing tries to keep the propeller upright"]
	quest.2E40755A354B1ACC.quest_desc: ["Outputs an analog signal that changes over time to match its input. "]
	quest.2EB2DFABB2B48B1D.quest_desc: ["The drone controller"]
	quest.2EC8420FC47F06F9.quest_desc: ["The **Tank** stores liquids. The **Pump** allows automated fluid transfer, and the **XP Pump** handles experience fluid. The **Battery** is for charging tools (if applicable)."]
	quest.2EC8420FC47F06F9.title: "Tank, Pump, Battery Upgrades"
	quest.2F17C0820C336EB5.quest_desc: ["The **Stack Upgrades** multiply the max stack size of items in the container, up to the **Omega Tier** which provides near-infinite storage for single item types."]
	quest.2F17C0820C336EB5.title: "Stack Upgrades (T1 to Omega)"
	quest.2F41C6CFFB43E38F.quest_desc: ["RIGHT CLICK to move you SHIFT HOLD RIGHT CLICK to move IT"]
	quest.2F5AD51B6A6C01A3.quest_desc: ["it breaks when overstressed "]
	quest.30151FE4EE927AA4.quest_desc: ["OVERSTRESS your machine when powered by redstone"]
	quest.308E1F5B53BFE9AB.quest_desc: ["Provides precise and adjustable rotational output"]
	quest.30FED0F5BD258790.quest_desc: ["Obtain the **Planar Stabilizer** component, which can be applied to either a **Tool Belt** or a **Bow**. Apply it to experience its balancing effect!"]
	quest.30FED0F5BD258790.title: "Achieving Planar Equilibrium"
	quest.318415495188777C.quest_desc: ["The **Earthpiercer** component is for single-headed tools (like shovels). It allows the tool to mine a straight line of five stone blocks. Using a lightweight handle also allows the player to throw the tool for distance mining."]
	quest.318415495188777C.title: "Deep Earth Penetrator"
	quest.31A3C643745E1953.quest_desc: ["The **Storage I/O** is a high-performance input/output block for pumping items into or out of the connected network. The **Decoration Table** is for coloring and cosmetic customization."]
	quest.31A3C643745E1953.title: "I/O Ports and Decoration"
	quest.31A7FF937593A5CC.quest_desc: ["Use an **Eye of Ender** to enhance your **Holosphere** with a scanner mode. This mode is vital for locating the structures containing relics needed to upgrade your hammer to the next quality tier."]
	quest.31A7FF937593A5CC.title: "Relic Detection Upgrade"
	quest.323398F25937EDBD.quest_desc: ["Provides redstone signal for navigation. Use a compas to link it to a lodestone"]
	quest.32C545450F2DBD65.quest_desc: ["Throw away EVERYTHING"]
	quest.33058894ACD9CB06.quest_desc: ["The **Graveyard** manages citizen mortality. If a citizen dies, they can be resurrected here using a specific resource (check the building GUI). It also employs the **Undertaker**."]
	quest.33058894ACD9CB06.title: "Support: Graveyard"
	quest.339EED71152EF112.quest_desc: ["Protect yourself from radiation by encasing your &2Reactor Rod&r in &3Reactor Glass&r"]
	quest.33A0198E1D098A1D.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.33B7579B8C040E54.quest_desc: ["The **Steampunk Armor** is the ultimate utility set: Helmet provides a hostile mob radar (on sneak), Chestplate features a clock/compass HUD, and the Leggings enable an emergency double jump, preventing all fall damage."]
	quest.33B7579B8C040E54.title: "Tier 3: Steampunk Utility and Tech"
	quest.33FC8F6543886276.quest_desc: ["The &9Physics Asembler&r infuses physics to anything its attached to. (you might want some honey glue for this)"]
	quest.340F5320DB6749AC.quest_desc: ["a medium tire"]
	quest.342A1EF584823D2C.quest_desc: ["The **Sawmill** and other workshops allow the Worker to craft items for the Builder. Ensure your Sawmill has the recipe for Torches to keep the colony safe at night."]
	quest.342A1EF584823D2C.title: "Torch Production"
	quest.34E39DE9EF4F080A.quest_desc: ["Engeneer's goggles for MAVRICS"]
	quest.34E6DA713B6DF25F.quest_desc: ["Macaw's provides LOTS of diferent blocks for building"]
	quest.34F3C116A5DDEA9D.quest_desc: ["Encased fans can produce thrust"]
	quest.359C4CAEFE608840.quest_desc: [
		"The only way to forge your tetra tool."
		"You need to right-click the crafting table to build it."
		"Many vanilla tool can be upgrade or change form in workbench."
		"You can see in the quest tab for tetra."
	]
	quest.359C4CAEFE608840.title: "Better crafting table"
	quest.35AE07F6A0F11A4D.quest_desc: [
		"The **Mechanical Spawner** is a kinetic block that spawns the mob type in the Soul Catcher placed inside."
		"It requires **Rotational Force (Kinetic Energy)** and a supply of **liquid**, such as liquid potions, via pipes."
		"It needs a minimum of **128 RPM**."
		"Its stress impact depends on the contained mob's max health, but is capped at **80 SU / RPM** by default."
		"Right-click with an empty hand or a wrench to configure the spawning area."
	]
	quest.35AE07F6A0F11A4D.quest_subtitle: "A kinetic block for spawning"
	quest.35AE07F6A0F11A4D.title: "The Mechanical Spawner"
	quest.35F368749ADA0A9A.quest_desc: ["glue two simulated contraptions together"]
	quest.360E9E02A494217C.quest_desc: ["The **Barracks Tower** is an upgraded, high-defense version of the guard tower. Guards stationed here are more effective and have a longer range of vision."]
	quest.360E9E02A494217C.title: "Military: Barracks Tower"
	quest.36777FCDAA9ABDF7.quest_desc: ["The **Tool Swapper** automatically switches your current tool to the best one for the job when you break a block. Extremely useful for quick mining and tree felling."]
	quest.36777FCDAA9ABDF7.quest_subtitle: "Always use the right tool."
	quest.36777FCDAA9ABDF7.title: "Tool Swapper Upgrades"
	quest.3681C21A44EBD0C0.quest_desc: ["Discovering a **Tools of War scroll** unlocks the **Warforge** feature for tools not primarily designed for combat."]
	quest.3681C21A44EBD0C0.title: "Scroll of the Warforge"
	quest.369CB78ACDDB0A88.quest_desc: ["Obtain a **Ham**! Ham is a valuable meat that can be cooked over a campfire or used in high-tier recipes. Try cooking the **Honey Glazed Ham Block**!"]
	quest.369CB78ACDDB0A88.title: "A Tasty Cut"
	quest.37BE190EE466D697.quest_desc: ["Upgrading the **Town Hall to Level 5** is the final stage of the original Town Hall structure, granting maximum influence and unlocking all available base features."]
	quest.37BE190EE466D697.title: "Town Hall Level 5 (MAX)"
	quest.37E43341FA234E84.quest_desc: ["The **Florist Hut** focuses on growing and collecting flowers and tall grass, producing dyes and other decorative resources."]
	quest.37E43341FA234E84.title: "Production: Florist Hut"
	quest.3806D43A958A0751.quest_desc: ["Detects blocks that obstruct its laser pointer, can be filtered for specific blocks"]
	quest.38E452884834812E.quest_desc: ["**Schematic Scrolls** grant special, unique abilities and modules for your **Tetra** tools."]
	quest.38E452884834812E.title: "Craftsman's Blueprints"
	quest.390F025F4B6316CA.quest_desc: ["Both Chipped and Rechiseled blocks can be automated with create or made in your backpack!"]
	quest.3A6250944C41A0BF.quest_desc: ["The **Earthpiercer** component is for single-headed tools (like shovels). It allows the tool to mine a straight line of five stone blocks. Using a lightweight handle also allows the player to throw the tool for distance mining."]
	quest.3A6250944C41A0BF.title: "Deep Earth Penetrator"
	quest.3AE1C3290500638F.quest_desc: ["Your colony has grown to a population of **10** citizens! You will need to build more residences and ensure a steady food supply to keep growing."]
	quest.3AE1C3290500638F.title: "Population Milestone: 10 Citizens"
	quest.3B40A769EDB26EA2.quest_desc: ["The **Postbox** and **Stash** blocks are essential for the **Deliveryman** to properly manage and move resources around the colony."]
	quest.3B40A769EDB26EA2.title: "Craft Logistics Blocks"
	quest.3B91163DE3DA885C.quest_desc: ["The **Nether Worker Hut** is key for automating the collection of essential Nether-only resources like Netherrack and Quartz, allowing your colony to grow into the mid-game."]
	quest.3B91163DE3DA885C.title: "Production: Nether Worker Hut"
	quest.3DD65447EA2C0EEF.quest_desc: ["A steam powered burner for generating LOTS of hot air"]
	quest.3E6032E2197B8FFB.quest_desc: ["requires HONEY! (Its worth it trust me)"]
	quest.3F8DE97B1961FA95.quest_desc: ["Continuously upgrade your tool belt to unlock maximum utility and convenience. Follow the material progression: **Wool** $\\rightarrow$ **Leather** $\\rightarrow$ **Iron** $\\rightarrow$ **Shulker Shell**."]
	quest.3F8DE97B1961FA95.title: "Ultimate Tool Rig"
	quest.3FBF1E57D4EDF26A.quest_desc: ["Upgrade your drill with a Diamond Drill!"]
	quest.3FBF1E57D4EDF26A.title: "Breaking the Hard Stuff"
	quest.3FD5AC591D225E2A.quest_desc: ["toss your exp into storage! easy peasy!"]
	quest.400175B13253B839.quest_desc: ["Like enchanting books, **Hone Scrolls** can be upgraded through a crafting interface. Combine scrolls to reach the maximum level and unlock the full potential of your **Hone** ability!"]
	quest.400175B13253B839.title: "Maximizing the Hone"
	quest.401990422501F5A3.quest_desc: [
		"Place your **Soul Catcher** into the **Mechanical Spawner**, supply the required liquid (check JEI for recipes, e.g., liquid Regeneration Potion), and give it a minimum of **128 RPM**."
